President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. met with President Volodymyr Zelenskyy of Ukraine to express the United States' support for Ukraine in defending its sovereignty and democracy against Russia's invasion. President Biden announced an additional $375 million in ammunition and equipment to meet Ukraine's immediate battlefield needs and to enhance its long-term capacity to deter Russian aggression. The leaders discussed plans to train Ukrainian pilots on fourth-generation fighter aircraft, such as the F-16, and to strengthen Ukraine's air defenses against missile and drone attacks. The United States and other G7 nations also expressed their support for Ukraine's reconstruction efforts, including the rebuilding of its energy infrastructure, and urged Ukraine to implement necessary reforms to fulfill its Euro-Atlantic aspirations. President Biden commended President Zelenskyy's commitment to a just peace based on the principles of the United Nations Charter.